<HL>
   French Crude Steel Output
</HL>
<DATE>
07/13/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   PARIS -- French companies produced 1,713,000 metric tons
of crude steel in June, up 1.7% from a year earlier, the
National Steel Manufacturers' Association said. A metric ton
is equal to about 2,204.62 pounds.
   The June result brings French output for the first half of
this year to 9,947,000 metric tons, down 3.7% from a year
earlier.
</LP>
<TEXT>
