<HL>
   Financing Business:
   Lazare Kaplan International Inc.
</HL>
<DATE>
07/13/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C15
</SO>
<CO>
   LKI
</CO>
<IN>
STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)
</IN>
<LP>
   LAZARE KAPLAN INTERNATIONAL Inc. said it plans a public
offering of one million common shares, with proceeds to be
used to pay down short-term debt. The New York-based
distributor of diamonds and jewelry said it filed a
registration statement with the Securities and Exchange
Commission and expects the offering to begin in mid-August.
It currently has about 3.1 million shares outstanding and
short-term debt of about $22.5 million. Lazare said the
offering will be managed by Wertheim Schroder &amp; Co.
</LP>
