<LP>
   OTTAWA -- Canadian steel ingot production totaled 224,171
metric tons in the week ended Saturday, down 20% from 280,137
tons in the preceeding week and down 27% from 306,731 tons a
year earlier, said Statistics Canada, a government agency.
   The cumulative total in 1990 was 7,493,148 tons, down 9.5%
from 8,279,327 tons a year ago.
