<HL>
   Business Brief -- MNC Financial Inc.:
   Quarterly Loss to Result
   From Loan Reserves Rise
</HL>
<DATE>
07/13/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4A
</SO>
<CO>
   MNC
</CO>
<IN>
BANKS (BNK)
</IN>
<LP>
   MNC Financial Inc., a Baltimore-based financial services
company, said it expects to post a second-quarter loss of
about $75 million, or 90 cents a fully diluted share,
primarily because of a 71% increase in loan-loss reserves,
and a write-off.
   In the year-earlier quarter, MNC earned $66.6 million, or
78 cents a fully diluted share.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company said it completed a review of its loan
portfolios and expects to increase second-quarter loan-loss
reserves by about $230 million, bringing total reserves to
about $550 million. MNC also said it plans to report a $94
million write-off for nonperforming loans in the quarter.
</TEXT>
