<LP>
   MONTREAL -- Caisse de Depot et Placement, the Quebec
government's pension-fund agency, named Guy Savard executive
vice president and chief operating officer, a new post.
   The appointment was expected. As reported, Mr. Savard was
named a director May 30. Mr. Savard will be responsible for
investment operations at Caisse de Depot, which manages close
to 40 billion Canadian dollars ($34.52 billion) of provincial
pension and insurance funds.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Mr. Savard reports to Jean-Claude Delorme, chairman and
general manager since July 1. As reported, Mr. Delorme
succeeded Jean Campeau, who becomes chairman of Domtar Inc.,
a Montreal forest products concern, this fall.
   Mr. Savard was vice president of Raymond, Chabot, Martin,
Pare, an accounting firm.
