<HL>
   Car Output to Rise
   By 32.2% This Week
</HL>
<DATE>
07/13/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B8
</SO>
<CO>
   GM F C HMC NSANY J.MZD SBRU J.IZM J.MOT TOYOY
</CO>
<IN>
AUTOMOBILES (AUT)
</IN>
<LP>
   DETROIT -- The 10 major U.S. auto makers planned to build
72,982 cars this week, a 32.2% increase from the 55,188 cars
built a year earlier.
   Ford Motor Co. said all its assembly plants except one
will reopen Monday following its annual two-week summer
break. The Dearborn, Mich., production facility that builds
the Mustang will be idled an additional week because of a
"shortage of dealer orders." About 2,100 workers will be
affected.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In June, the 10 major U.S. auto makers built 992,101 cars
and trucks, a 2% increase from the 972,678 built a year
earlier.
   U.S. car output was virtually unchanged in June, and truck
and bus production increased 4.4% from the year-earlier
month.
