weaker earnings in the chemical and petrochemical sector, but
that this will be offset partly by "higher yields" in some
other areas and by benefits of lower taxes.
   He said that for all of 1990, the company expects again to
record a good year in general, but he wasn't more specific.
VEBA's 1989 profit rose 14% from a year earlier to 1.25
billion marks, on a 12% increase in sales to 49.9 billion
marks.
